eu.cqse.check.framework.typetracker

Class TypedVariable

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.cqse.check.framework.typetracker.TypedVariable
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class TypedVariable
extends Object
implements Serializable
    A typed variable is an immutable object that contains information about the type of a variable. It stores the variable's name, the variable's type and further modifiers. The type is stored as string, that represents the concatenation of all contained token texts. Thus for field private static java.util.List<String> names; the variable name "names", the modifiers ["private", "static"] and the type name "java.util.List<String>" will be stored.
